content.description: Start on the sloping rail under the roof, where you start can change the grade but just do whatever feels best. Prefrom some large roof moves on positive holds out to the lip to the right. Use arcane magic to preform a foot-plant-hand-foot-match-mantle on the two opposing sloping rails, without dabbing, and topout into the high country to your left.Â The crux is not dabbing but the move to escape the dab is kinda fun. Fall on the slab is a bit scary aswell.
content.location: Start under the roof and trend right

content.description: Start down low on an undercling jug, Climb up the arete using a bomber heel hook and crimps on the face. Pinch the arete like theres no tomorrow and turn the corner on bad crimps and bad feet, to lunge to a good side pull top out straight up on.lower start
content.location: On the other side of the Lunch boulder from Sack Lunch, just off the trail.

content.description: Large boulder with assorted rooves, great place for hikers to picnic and gawk at you as you top out
